00:03:37.680 --> 00:03:40.202
Obviously, haven't
done it very exactly,

00:03:40.202 --> 00:03:41.660
but our line is
going to look like.

00:03:41.660 --> 00:03:45.090
That's going to be a pretty
steep upward-sloping line.

00:03:45.090 --> 00:03:46.902
It has a very high
slope, slope of seven.

00:03:46.902 --> 00:03:48.360
If you move one in
the x direction,

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:49.920
you have to move up seven.

00:03:49.920 --> 00:03:53.410
And its y-intercept
